WEBVTT

01:35.356 --> 01:37.227
I knew something like this
was gonna happen.

01:37.271 --> 01:38.272
Please, stop.
She's gonna be okay.

01:38.315 --> 01:39.795
Is it there?

01:39.838 --> 01:42.232
I knew something like this
was gonna happen.

01:42.276 --> 01:44.713
Loretta, you can't smoke
at a hospital!

01:44.756 --> 01:47.281
There are sick people
everywhere, and newborns!

01:48.891 --> 01:51.111
-She awake yet?
-Not yet, honey.

01:51.154 --> 01:52.155
Where's Sharon?

01:52.199 --> 01:53.374
Oh, she's getting candy.

01:53.417 --> 01:55.245
-Oh, Mom.
-Hey!

01:55.289 --> 01:56.942
-Brother from another mother.
-Hey, man.

01:56.986 --> 01:58.335
She ain't awake yet.

01:58.379 --> 01:59.684
It's gotta be okay.

01:59.728 --> 02:01.295
-Where's Sharon?
-I'm right here.

02:01.338 --> 02:03.993
-Hey, Sis.
-Oh, my God!

02:04.036 --> 02:06.648
Hey, where are my Milk Duds?

02:06.691 --> 02:08.215
I forgot.

02:08.258 --> 02:09.912
Did you get Bea a balloon?

02:09.955 --> 02:12.001
I think it has a hole in it.

02:12.044 --> 02:13.959
It's okay maybe we can
exchange it later.

02:14.003 --> 02:18.050
What? What is wrong
with you guys? Bea is in a coma.

02:18.094 --> 02:20.575
And you guys are talking
about balloons and candies.

02:20.618 --> 02:22.054
I eat when I get nervous.

02:22.098 --> 02:24.187
We never should've let her
come back here.

02:24.231 --> 02:26.058
Honey, breathe.
Honey, breathe.

02:26.102 --> 02:27.756
Yeah, breathe.
You're not helping.

02:27.799 --> 02:29.279
-She's not helping?
-You know what, Loretta?

02:29.323 --> 02:31.542
Have you ever helped?
All you do is criticize.

02:31.586 --> 02:33.196
I've always felt trapped
in this family.

02:33.240 --> 02:35.894
But this is whole other level.

02:35.938 --> 02:38.680
Usually, when I need
to get away, I go for a run.

02:38.723 --> 02:41.987
I'd give anything to be able
to do that right now.

02:42.031 --> 02:44.207
Everyone, remain calm.

02:44.251 --> 02:47.210
Alright. Thank you.

02:47.254 --> 02:50.213
Now remember, just because
Bea can't hear us

02:50.257 --> 02:51.780
doesn't mean she can't feel us.

02:51.823 --> 02:53.608
Ben's right.
We should all say a prayer.

02:53.651 --> 02:56.567
Well, that won't work,
you're Jewish.

02:56.611 --> 02:58.613
Jewish people pray too,
Loretta.

02:58.656 --> 03:00.354
Well, not like Catholics.

03:00.397 --> 03:01.920
And Bea is a Catholic.

03:01.964 --> 03:04.358
-No, I'm not.
-By blood.

03:04.401 --> 03:07.970
Loretta, would you like
to say the prayer?

03:08.013 --> 03:11.887
-Yes, I would. Thank you.
-What's the point?

03:11.930 --> 03:14.150
If there is a God,
he's the one who put me here.

03:16.239 --> 03:18.067
Heavenly Father,

03:18.110 --> 03:21.853
we humbly beseech you
to look down on our Bea

03:21.897 --> 03:24.813
and rain a holy vengeance

03:24.856 --> 03:27.642
on the goddamn motherfucker
who put her in here.

03:29.121 --> 03:30.732
God doesn't have to worry
about that.

03:30.775 --> 03:32.429
'Cause when I catch who it was

03:32.473 --> 03:34.388
I'mma beat the crap
out of him.

03:34.431 --> 03:36.303
I mean, I got a second degree
black belt.

03:36.346 --> 03:38.261
-No, he doesn't.
-We don't really know.

03:38.305 --> 03:39.610
That someone did this
to her yet.

03:39.654 --> 03:41.873
Okay, this could've been
an accident.

03:41.917 --> 03:43.962
But I don't have any memory
of that night.

03:44.006 --> 03:45.268
Was it night?

03:45.312 --> 03:47.792
Loretta, I swear to God...

03:47.836 --> 03:49.707
I told you, that won't work.

03:49.751 --> 03:51.187
Maybe I can remember what
happened

03:51.231 --> 03:52.971
if I just think real hard.

03:54.451 --> 03:56.627
Okay, new plan.

03:56.671 --> 03:59.108
Maybe I should try
retracing my steps.

03:59.151 --> 04:01.197
But where do you start
when the thing you lost

04:01.241 --> 04:02.546
is your last memory.

04:06.333 --> 04:09.205
Oh! Guess we're starting
way back.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.468
My parents couldn't wait
to have a baby.

04:12.643 --> 04:14.428
I said my parents!

04:14.471 --> 04:15.820
Hello!

04:17.909 --> 04:19.520
Now, that's obviously not them.

04:19.563 --> 04:22.218
My parents!
Mis padres.

04:22.262 --> 04:24.612
The ones who gave me life.

04:24.655 --> 04:27.658
Growing up, I was told
my parents were special.

04:27.702 --> 04:29.181
When I got old enough,

04:29.225 --> 04:31.053
I realized that's the word
adults use

04:31.096 --> 04:34.099
when someone has a disability.

04:34.143 --> 04:36.058
My dad was born
without a disability

04:36.101 --> 04:38.452
but he got hit by
a drunk driver when he was 12.

04:40.497 --> 04:42.499
After that,
his body kept growing

04:42.543 --> 04:45.807
but his mind just kind of
stayed the same.

04:45.850 --> 04:48.418
Part of my mom's brain
never fully developed.

04:48.462 --> 04:51.247
The doctors said she'd never
be able to live on her own.

04:51.291 --> 04:52.683
Who's that?

04:52.727 --> 04:55.077
Oh, the neighbors
recommended him.

04:55.120 --> 04:57.035
He looks thirsty.

04:57.079 --> 04:58.602
Can I bring him some lemonade?

04:59.995 --> 05:02.345
Oh, sure, sweetie.
That's nice.

05:02.389 --> 05:04.695
Don't let her go out there.

05:04.739 --> 05:07.089
-Why not?
-Look at her.

05:07.132 --> 05:11.136
The part of her brain that makes
her horny is still working.

05:11.180 --> 05:14.139
Earl! She just wants
to give him something to drink.

05:15.619 --> 05:18.927
The guy is in a tank top
for crying out loud.

05:25.499 --> 05:27.022
You wanna go on a date?

05:28.589 --> 05:31.461
-Sure.
-I'm Sharon.

05:31.505 --> 05:32.767
I'm Derek.

05:37.641 --> 05:40.165
Ah, where are you going?

05:40.209 --> 05:42.254
To ask my mom
if I can go on a date.

05:46.607 --> 05:48.652
I can't sleep.

05:48.696 --> 05:52.177
-Yeah, me neither.
-She should be home by now.

05:52.221 --> 05:54.397
I can't believe
you let her go out with him.

05:56.051 --> 05:58.140
Everyone says he is
a very nice young man.

05:58.183 --> 06:01.099
And she needs to be around
people her own age.

06:03.188 --> 06:04.973
She's not twenty-one
on the inside, Peg.

06:06.409 --> 06:08.716
Well, neither is Derek.

06:08.759 --> 06:10.631
How do you know?

06:10.674 --> 06:12.372
Doris McAllister told me

06:12.415 --> 06:15.505
he had a really bad head injury
when he was a boy.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.333
Doris McAllister also told you

06:17.377 --> 06:20.945
that she saw Elvis
at a Piggly Wiggly.

06:20.989 --> 06:23.774
Well, Sharon deserves this.
She deserves to be happy.

06:24.949 --> 06:26.342
I know.

06:28.213 --> 06:29.606
Don't worry.

06:29.650 --> 06:31.129
They just went out for pizza.

06:31.173 --> 06:33.262
What's the worst
that could happen?

06:41.401 --> 06:43.881
I love you, Mrs. Johnson.

06:43.925 --> 06:45.840
I love you, Mr. Johnson

06:54.979 --> 06:57.808
He gave her my mother's ring.

06:57.852 --> 06:59.375
Oh! That's nice.

07:03.292 --> 07:04.554
So, um...

07:04.598 --> 07:06.426
How-how long was your drive
up from Vegas?

07:06.469 --> 07:08.645
-Ah, too long.
-It was, it was long.

07:08.689 --> 07:10.430
Oh, I could imagine.

07:14.477 --> 07:19.047
Well, you know, I think it's
pretty clear what we need to do.

07:19.090 --> 07:20.788
I agree.

07:20.831 --> 07:22.964
-We need to get them a divorce.
-Sharon needs to be sterilized.

07:23.007 --> 07:24.226
Excuse me.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.663
I said,
"Sharon needs to be sterilized."

07:26.707 --> 07:28.186
We can't let 'em procreate.

07:28.230 --> 07:29.579
Why on earth would we do that

07:29.623 --> 07:30.841
when we can just
get them a divorce?

07:30.885 --> 07:32.626
Absolutely not.

07:32.669 --> 07:34.062
Divorce is a sin.

07:34.105 --> 07:36.238
My son's not gonna go to hell

07:36.281 --> 07:38.066
because of your trollop
of a daughter.

07:38.109 --> 07:39.676
-Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!
-Excuse me?

07:39.720 --> 07:43.288
-I said, my son's--
-Yes, I heard you. I heard you.

07:43.332 --> 07:45.900
Look, everyone.
Just calm-calm down.

07:45.943 --> 07:47.467
Yeah, calm down.
Did you hear what she said?

07:47.510 --> 07:50.600
I-I did and...she has a point.

07:50.644 --> 07:54.691
Ah, it's just I don't think
they can take care of a child.

07:54.735 --> 07:56.345
Earl, we're not getting
Sharon spayed.

07:56.388 --> 07:57.694
She's not a goddamn poodle.

07:57.738 --> 07:59.000
What choice do we have?

07:59.043 --> 08:00.567
Oh, you can get
your son neutered.

08:00.610 --> 08:03.918
-Mom! That's awful.
-Well, that's my point.

08:03.961 --> 08:06.224
Your father's the one who wants
to get your sister sterilized!

08:06.268 --> 08:07.791
Ah, I just said
we should consider it.

08:07.835 --> 08:09.489
Well, sure,
if you want to get sued.

08:09.532 --> 08:10.620
Oh, shut up, Hal.

08:10.664 --> 08:12.622
No, I'm-I'm just saying.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.798
My cousin's a lawyer.

08:14.842 --> 08:17.366
Two years ago
he worked with a woman

08:17.409 --> 08:19.542
who sued her parents
for this very thing.

08:19.586 --> 08:22.023
They took the poor folks
for all they had.

08:22.066 --> 08:25.287
Well, then, that's-that's
definitely out of the question.

08:25.330 --> 08:27.115
-We can't afford that.
-Oh, my God, dad!

08:27.158 --> 08:28.464
If that's all you care about,

08:28.508 --> 08:30.118
why don't you move
to North Korea

08:30.161 --> 08:31.902
and let the government
do it for you?

08:31.946 --> 08:33.295
'Cause I'm not
a goddamn communist!

08:33.338 --> 08:34.905
Okay, sweetie, sweetie.

08:34.949 --> 08:37.691
Maybe we're all, you know,
getting worked up over nothing.

08:37.734 --> 08:40.781
You know, maybe Derek and Sharon
aren't even interested in sex.

08:47.788 --> 08:50.530
Grandma Peg wasn't great
at predicting things.

08:52.140 --> 08:55.447
-What should we name her?
-Bambi.

08:55.491 --> 08:58.363
Now you know what Bea
is short for.

08:58.407 --> 09:00.278
Yeah, that's a sweet name.

09:01.584 --> 09:04.544
-Hi there, Bambi.
-Hi, Bambi.

09:04.587 --> 09:06.850
My mother named me after her
favorite cartoon character

09:06.894 --> 09:08.722
and my father had no idea

09:08.765 --> 09:12.595
he was increasing my chances of
becoming a stripper ten-fold.

09:12.639 --> 09:15.903
That's kind of like a metaphor
for my whole childhood.

09:15.946 --> 09:18.383
But hey,
at least we were happy.

09:21.604 --> 09:25.565
♪ If I weren't
in the spider web of mine ♪

09:25.608 --> 09:29.569
Oh, here I think
grandma wants to hold you.

09:32.180 --> 09:33.877
You're such a good baby.

09:34.922 --> 09:36.488
Who's a cute baby?

09:40.492 --> 09:42.364
I did it!

09:42.407 --> 09:44.758
-Good morning, Peg.
-Hi, dad.

09:45.976 --> 09:48.805
Grandpa is back.

09:48.849 --> 09:53.810
♪ Don't wanna hurt
my dear love of my life ♪♪

09:53.854 --> 09:56.639
Oh! Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

09:56.683 --> 09:58.075
-Okay.
-Okay, okay, okay, okay.

09:58.119 --> 10:01.557
-Why are you guys so loud?
-Sorry, sorry.

10:01.601 --> 10:03.385
Sorry.

10:03.428 --> 10:05.039
We can't do this all life.

10:05.082 --> 10:06.910
You see, I knew something like
this was gonna happen.

10:06.954 --> 10:09.783
Oh, please.
It could happen to anybody.

10:09.826 --> 10:11.828
But you remember
that time I almost sat on Joy.

10:11.872 --> 10:13.787
I'd have squashed her
if you hadn't been there.

10:13.830 --> 10:15.876
I'm done saving babies
from getting squashed!

10:15.919 --> 10:17.965
-I'm not raising another kid!
-No, you're right.

10:18.008 --> 10:19.793
You're not.
Derek and Sharon are.

10:19.836 --> 10:21.882
-Oh, stop it.
-Stop what?

10:21.925 --> 10:24.058
Pretending.
This is all pretend.

10:24.101 --> 10:25.189
And they're playing house.

10:25.233 --> 10:26.669
They are not playing house.

10:26.713 --> 10:28.149
Oh, Honey, I'm home!

10:30.107 --> 10:31.500
Where have you been?

10:31.543 --> 10:33.937
-Hi, honey.
-Oh, out looking for a job.

10:33.981 --> 10:36.157
I mean, we need to
get our own place.

10:36.200 --> 10:38.507
What?
Is that my brief case?

10:40.161 --> 10:41.684
What?
It's snake skin.

10:41.728 --> 10:44.295
Derek, Derek, no one
needs to move out.

10:44.339 --> 10:45.340
Oh, yes. We do.

10:45.383 --> 10:46.863
I mean...

10:46.907 --> 10:49.605
A man needs to provide a home
for his family.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.128
Right, Earl?

10:51.172 --> 10:53.304
-Is this your idea?
-No.

10:53.348 --> 10:55.916
Look, um, tell you what, Derek,

10:55.959 --> 10:58.309
if this is what you really want,
you know, when the time comes,

10:58.353 --> 11:00.660
we'll help you find
an apartment nearby

11:00.703 --> 11:01.835
you know when
Bea is little older.

11:01.878 --> 11:03.314
No, it cannot work.

11:03.358 --> 11:05.055
There ain't any jobs
around here.

11:05.099 --> 11:07.667
And, uh, I mean,
I want to be closer to mom.

11:07.710 --> 11:10.452
So, we're going to Vegas.

11:10.495 --> 11:13.063
-No! No one is going anywhere.
-Relax.

11:13.107 --> 11:15.805
You're not taking
Sharon to Vegas.

11:15.849 --> 11:17.459
Because you do not know
what's best for her.

11:17.502 --> 11:19.679
-Yes, I do.
-I can get a job at Hooters.

11:19.722 --> 11:21.724
-Good idea.
-No, you can't.

11:21.768 --> 11:24.466
You can't. You cannot take care
of Bea by yourself.

11:24.509 --> 11:27.730
Yes, I can. Bambi is my baby.
She is not yours.

11:27.774 --> 11:29.514
I know that, sweetheart.
I know, I know. Careful.

11:29.558 --> 11:31.734
You know what,
we don't need your help anymore

11:31.778 --> 11:33.736
or-or anyone else's.

11:33.780 --> 11:35.477
I can take care
of my own family.

11:37.479 --> 11:38.959
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

11:41.657 --> 11:43.006
Why didn't you say something?

11:43.050 --> 11:45.617
I told you,
I'm not raising another kid.

11:45.661 --> 11:48.229
We've been raising Sharon
for 21 years.

11:48.272 --> 11:49.447
How can you be so selfish?

11:49.491 --> 11:51.014
Oh, get off your high horse.

11:51.058 --> 11:52.537
You knew, it was gonna
end up like this.

11:52.581 --> 11:53.756
What?

11:53.800 --> 11:55.845
You're the one that said
Sharon can date.

11:55.889 --> 11:57.934
You're the one who said
she can have babies.

11:57.978 --> 12:00.197
-I'm the one who tried to stop.
-I wanted her to have a--

12:00.241 --> 12:01.503
You wanted her out!

12:01.546 --> 12:03.200
I don't have a lot...
Oh, my God!

12:03.244 --> 12:04.767
How can you say that to me?

12:04.811 --> 12:06.073
-Well, listen.
-How can you say that to me?

12:06.116 --> 12:08.162
Don't make me the bad guy.

12:08.205 --> 12:11.252
Because I know
you feel relieved too.

12:30.010 --> 12:31.359
Hello?

12:32.839 --> 12:34.318
Are you Loretta Johnson?

12:34.362 --> 12:35.711
Oh, Lord, no.

12:36.886 --> 12:39.019
Okay, Peg Addleman?

12:39.062 --> 12:42.413
McDonald, I went back
to my maiden name.

12:42.457 --> 12:44.764
-Noted.
-And you are?

12:44.807 --> 12:46.461
I'm Mary.
Bea's social worker.

12:46.504 --> 12:48.332
What is she doing here?

12:48.376 --> 12:49.769
-Oh!
-Yes.

12:49.812 --> 12:51.771
Why-why does Bea have
a social worker?

12:51.814 --> 12:55.383
It's routine when minors
come in with injuries.

12:55.426 --> 12:58.342
I do my report and provide it
to the proper authorities.

12:58.386 --> 12:59.779
What do they think happened?

12:59.822 --> 13:01.519
Well, they think
it's likely an accident.

13:02.433 --> 13:03.957
What do you think?

13:04.000 --> 13:06.524
No, I just want to make sure
there's nothing else to it.

13:09.310 --> 13:12.008
I actually met Bea before.

13:12.052 --> 13:14.619
Seven years ago,
after the car accident.

13:14.663 --> 13:16.970
Ugh, they made
such a big deal out of that.

13:17.013 --> 13:19.363
That-that was just
a big misunderstanding.

13:19.407 --> 13:21.104
It's okay.

13:21.148 --> 13:22.932
I'm actually more interested
in what happened yesterday.

13:24.064 --> 13:25.500
Please, have a seat.

13:25.543 --> 13:27.197
Um, it's okay
that we do it here?

13:27.241 --> 13:28.895
I-I don't wanna leave Bea.

13:28.938 --> 13:33.464
Everybody else went home
to rest and change and...

13:33.508 --> 13:35.510
But you stayed.

13:35.553 --> 13:39.383
Well, somebody had to.
And-and I-I wanted to.

13:41.081 --> 13:43.213
My-my ex-husband
was supposed to show up

13:43.257 --> 13:45.085
and he could've stayed
but you know...

13:45.128 --> 13:46.521
Surprise, surprise!

13:48.349 --> 13:50.612
Ex-husband.

13:50.655 --> 13:52.527
I-I don't know
how much help I'll be.

13:52.570 --> 13:54.311
I was in California yesterday

13:54.355 --> 13:56.705
that's where I live.

13:56.748 --> 13:58.315
That's okay. Um...

13:58.359 --> 14:00.361
Actually, I-I'd like to get
a bigger picture

14:00.404 --> 14:02.189
of Bea's life.

14:02.232 --> 14:03.843
For example...

14:03.886 --> 14:06.933
has she been getting along
with her parents lately?

14:06.976 --> 14:09.849
Oh, Derek and Sharon
had nothing to do with this.

14:09.892 --> 14:13.591
I'm not saying that,
that they do. Just, um...

14:13.635 --> 14:16.420
I know, Bea's childhood was
somewhat non-traditional.

14:16.464 --> 14:19.075
Oh, my God, You live in a van
with your parents one time

14:19.119 --> 14:20.947
and they never let it go.

14:22.426 --> 14:25.429
I mean, it was a nice van.

14:25.473 --> 14:27.823
Dad said the only time
he took money from grandpa

14:27.867 --> 14:29.172
was to buy it.

14:30.695 --> 14:32.262
♪ Here I go again

14:32.306 --> 14:35.526
♪ On my own

14:35.570 --> 14:40.749
♪ Goin' down the only road
I've ever known ♪

14:40.792 --> 14:42.882
We moved into
this really neat community

14:42.925 --> 14:45.580
where my parents
could just be themselves.

14:45.623 --> 14:46.886
Look at this place.

14:46.929 --> 14:49.540
-Wow! Yeah.
-Huh?

14:49.584 --> 14:52.761
I think it was the first time
my mom had real friends.

14:52.804 --> 14:54.589
So, there was always someone
to watch me

14:54.632 --> 14:56.460
while my parents
went to look for jobs.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.698
When no one wanted
to hire my dad...

15:16.741 --> 15:18.178
he made his own opportunity.

15:19.744 --> 15:21.572
Say what you want
about my parents

15:21.616 --> 15:25.272
but when they actually commit
to doing something, they do it.

15:25.315 --> 15:27.187
♪ Here I go again

15:27.230 --> 15:30.320
♪ On my own

15:30.364 --> 15:33.933
♪ Goin' down the only road
I've ever known ♪

15:35.891 --> 15:39.025
♪ Like a drifter
I was born to walk alone ♪

15:39.068 --> 15:42.942
Dad said living in that van
was the happiest we ever were.

15:42.985 --> 15:45.596
But he wanted us
to have a real home.

15:45.640 --> 15:47.642
And eventually,
we moved into one.

15:50.297 --> 15:52.125
Huh?

15:54.692 --> 15:57.434
Dad told me
we were happy in the van,

15:57.478 --> 16:00.524
but I remember being
really happy in the house.

16:02.483 --> 16:06.400
♪ Like a drifter
I was born to walk alone ♪

16:08.706 --> 16:11.622
♪ 'Cause I know
what it means ♪♪

17:08.070 --> 17:11.595
I liked that my parents trusted
me to take care of myself.

17:11.639 --> 17:13.815
Until they started trusting me
to do everything.

17:13.858 --> 17:16.252
I don't see
why this is so hard.

17:16.296 --> 17:17.732
I mean, okay.

17:17.775 --> 17:19.951
Look, next time
when you press the gas--

17:19.995 --> 17:22.215
-What are you doing?
-You said, "Press the gas."

17:22.258 --> 17:23.477
-I wasn't done!
-Don't yell at me!

17:23.520 --> 17:25.348
-I'm not yelling!
-Yes, you are.

17:28.656 --> 17:30.092
I don't wanna do this anymore.

17:30.136 --> 17:32.616
You said it would be fun
and it's not fun!

17:32.660 --> 17:34.357
You gotta learn to drive.

17:34.401 --> 17:35.576
I'm ten.

17:38.448 --> 17:40.581
What if there's an emergency
and I can't drive?

17:42.365 --> 17:43.584
What kind of emergency?

17:46.761 --> 17:50.199
I don't know.
What if my leg fell off?

17:51.287 --> 17:53.333
Or I drank too many beers?

17:53.376 --> 17:54.682
Why can't mom drive?

17:57.293 --> 17:59.817
Because your mama can't get
a license, that's why.

18:05.388 --> 18:07.216
Is that because she's retarded?

18:09.305 --> 18:10.915
Who told you that?

18:10.959 --> 18:12.221
Esther did.

18:14.223 --> 18:15.833
She told everyone at school.

18:17.531 --> 18:19.620
Your mama is not retarded.

18:26.975 --> 18:28.672
Are you retarded?

18:28.716 --> 18:31.110
No! Ain't nobody retarded!

18:43.339 --> 18:44.688
Look, if you...

18:45.820 --> 18:47.735
if you learn to drive...

18:51.042 --> 18:52.783
I'll get you
anything you want.

18:58.833 --> 19:00.704
Anything?

19:02.358 --> 19:05.144
Godzilla, sit.

19:06.232 --> 19:07.537
Good boy.

19:08.234 --> 19:09.713
Good boy.

19:09.757 --> 19:12.281
Okay, now let's tr...

19:13.761 --> 19:15.371
-Let's try "Stay."
-Bambi!

19:16.372 --> 19:18.331
My name is Bea!

19:18.374 --> 19:21.682
-Bea!
-What? I'm busy.

19:21.725 --> 19:23.684
Your mom needs help
getting dressed for work!

19:24.467 --> 19:25.773
Come on!

19:25.816 --> 19:26.991
Okay.

19:27.775 --> 19:29.646
Thanks.

19:29.690 --> 19:31.648
Let's go get mommy ready
for work.

19:36.087 --> 19:37.611
Where're you going?

19:37.654 --> 19:40.179
The track.
Bob's picking me up.

19:41.354 --> 19:42.529
But it's Saturday.

19:42.572 --> 19:46.185
Well, I'm not working.
I'm racing.

19:46.228 --> 19:48.056
What about my soccer game?

19:48.099 --> 19:50.189
Well, I'll come next weekend.

19:53.409 --> 19:54.758
Bye, Bea.

19:58.936 --> 20:01.200
Mom, what are you doing?

20:01.243 --> 20:02.505
Have you brushed your teeth?

20:02.549 --> 20:03.941
Yeah.

20:03.985 --> 20:05.116
Then why aren't you dressed?

20:05.160 --> 20:06.857
I'm getting a snack first.

20:06.901 --> 20:09.295
No, you're gonna be late
and you can't get fired again

20:09.338 --> 20:11.601
because dad's truck
isn't enough.

20:13.603 --> 20:15.126
Godzilla, leave it.

20:47.507 --> 20:49.813
Okay, let's go get dressed.

20:52.773 --> 20:55.254
Come on, Mom. I'll walk you to
the bus on the way to my game.

20:56.690 --> 20:59.432
Godzilla?

20:59.475 --> 21:00.650
Godzilla!

21:03.740 --> 21:05.873
Mom, did you go outside?

21:05.916 --> 21:08.528
Yeah. I wanted to see
if it was sunny out.

21:08.571 --> 21:10.225
Why didn't you just
look out a window?

21:11.400 --> 21:12.662
Godzilla!

21:14.360 --> 21:15.752
Godzilla!

21:19.278 --> 21:21.236
This is definitely an emergency.

21:39.472 --> 21:41.387
So, you have no idea
how this happened?

21:43.345 --> 21:44.999
Nope.

21:45.042 --> 21:46.479
You weren't driving?

21:47.610 --> 21:48.829
Lady, I'm ten.

21:51.919 --> 21:53.660
Did your dad tell you to lie?

21:53.703 --> 21:55.052
He definitely did.

21:55.792 --> 21:57.054
No.

22:04.975 --> 22:06.150
Can I see my dog now?

22:07.804 --> 22:10.416
You can get Godzilla back
when we're done.

22:14.420 --> 22:15.769
I don't want him back.

22:17.379 --> 22:21.035
Really? After you crashed
a car trying to find him?

22:21.078 --> 22:22.645
I told you. That wasn't me.

22:27.955 --> 22:29.391
I wanna say goodbye.

22:32.176 --> 22:34.222
I can't take care of him
and my mom.

22:36.877 --> 22:38.748
It's natural for a big sister

22:38.792 --> 22:40.533
to feel protective
of her little sister.

22:40.576 --> 22:42.404
And for an aunt to feel
protective of her niece.

22:42.448 --> 22:46.626
I think I just feel that
a little more intensely.

22:46.669 --> 22:47.931
Um...

22:47.975 --> 22:51.587
So, when Bea was born

22:51.631 --> 22:53.981
we wondered
if it wouldn't be better

22:54.024 --> 22:56.418
for everyone if we took her in.

22:56.462 --> 22:58.768
Right, right, but then we got
pregnant with the twins

22:58.812 --> 23:00.901
and, you know, as you
can imagine, our hands full.

23:00.944 --> 23:04.078
And Sharon was so good with Bea
when she was a baby.

23:04.121 --> 23:05.775
-She was, surely was.
-But...

23:05.819 --> 23:07.777
After the...

23:09.562 --> 23:13.087
car incident,
we revisited the idea

23:13.130 --> 23:15.655
and Bea came to stay
with us for the summer.

23:19.441 --> 23:21.225
Slice this up for you, buddy.

23:21.269 --> 23:23.184
Hey, good work
on the avocado toast by the way.

23:23.227 --> 23:24.707
-Thanks.
-It's good, right?

23:24.751 --> 23:27.188
Fruit's fresh today,
I love this farmer's market.

23:27.231 --> 23:28.798
Alright, here you go.

23:28.842 --> 23:30.800
So good.

23:30.844 --> 23:32.323
I, I know it's further

23:32.367 --> 23:35.109
but I'm gonna
go to this one the next time.

23:35.152 --> 23:37.633
Oh, those blueberries
are fantastic.

23:37.677 --> 23:40.244
These are organic and they're
like a, they're beautiful.

23:40.288 --> 23:43.030
So, like super concentrated
super--

23:43.073 --> 23:44.640
What's wrong with you guys?

23:46.686 --> 23:48.862
-Bea, why would you ask that?
-All the medicine.

23:48.905 --> 23:52.605
Oh! Honey, those are vitamins.
Would you like some?

23:52.648 --> 23:54.041
We don't want you to get sick
and there's been some

23:54.084 --> 23:56.522
really yucky stuff going around.

23:56.565 --> 23:57.827
I'm good.

23:57.871 --> 23:59.002
-Mom?
-Mm-hmm.

23:59.046 --> 24:00.830
Do I have tennis practice today?

24:00.874 --> 24:04.791
No. You have tutoring
and then therapy.

24:05.966 --> 24:07.228
Ow! Ow! I cut myself!

24:07.271 --> 24:08.490
Oh, alright.

24:08.534 --> 24:10.013
Is it bad?
Let me see.

24:10.057 --> 24:12.189
That's why we do it for you,
buddy.

24:13.539 --> 24:15.366
-Have to see the damage.
-Mama's on it.

24:15.410 --> 24:17.151
-How is it?
-Oh, it's a good one.

24:17.194 --> 24:19.719
-Yeah, is that a real one now?
-You're gonna be okay, look.

24:19.762 --> 24:21.851
-Your boo-boo buddy.
-That felt better?

24:21.895 --> 24:23.462
You'll be just fine.

24:24.898 --> 24:26.813
What's for dessert?

24:26.856 --> 24:28.815
We don't do dessert
for breakfast.

24:28.858 --> 24:30.381
Well, that fucking blows.

24:38.389 --> 24:40.217
Okay, um, you know what, Bea,

24:40.261 --> 24:41.958
I think we gotta talk about
some ground rules.

24:42.002 --> 24:43.264
Okay?

24:43.307 --> 24:45.658
So, we don't use foul language.

24:45.701 --> 24:47.790
We cover our mouth
when we belch.

24:47.834 --> 24:50.358
And in this house, kiddo,

24:50.401 --> 24:51.664
we wear pants at the table.

24:51.707 --> 24:53.317
I'm letting my boys breathe.

24:55.711 --> 24:57.844
Okay.
Why don't you guys go out?

24:57.887 --> 24:59.149
You guys are done, right?

24:59.193 --> 25:01.064
Let's go out and play.

25:01.108 --> 25:03.371
Yes, yes, yes, yes!
Thank you, mom!

25:03.414 --> 25:05.982
And be careful on the steps,
please.

25:06.026 --> 25:07.810
Those steps are too steep.

25:07.854 --> 25:10.378
She's like a feral dog.

25:10.421 --> 25:11.901
-Ben!
-What?

25:11.945 --> 25:14.164
Y-you know what I found
her doing the other day?

25:14.208 --> 25:16.210
She was using Oreos
to train the boys

25:16.253 --> 25:17.864
to fetch the remote for her.

25:21.345 --> 25:22.999
You guys wanna go swimming?

25:23.043 --> 25:24.348
We're not allowed to swim alone.

25:24.392 --> 25:25.436
-Yeah.
-You're not alone.

25:25.480 --> 25:27.090
You're with me.

25:27.134 --> 25:28.657
Come on!
I know you want to.

25:31.051 --> 25:33.619
Please just try to
connect with her?

25:33.662 --> 25:37.666
I have. I really have.
I even gave her my lucky hat.

25:37.710 --> 25:41.061
Aww. You've had that hat
since college. That's so sweet.

25:41.104 --> 25:43.411
It's incredibly sweet.
Yeah, you know what she did?

25:43.454 --> 25:45.935
She threw it in her bag
and then flipped me off

25:45.979 --> 25:48.938
when I told her that
she couldn't borrow the car

25:48.982 --> 25:51.811
Bea, are you okay? Bea!

25:51.854 --> 25:54.596
Mom, dad, it's Bea.
Come quick!

25:54.640 --> 25:55.989
-She can't swim.
-Bea, I'm coming.

25:56.032 --> 25:58.687
-She can't swim.
-Hold on!

25:58.731 --> 26:00.167
Hey!

26:02.299 --> 26:04.780
-Oh, my God. Are you okay?
-I got you. I got you.

26:04.824 --> 26:06.956
-Are you okay? Oh, my God!
-You okay? You okay?

26:07.000 --> 26:09.089
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

26:09.132 --> 26:12.527
Bea, Bea, that was
incredibly dangerous.

26:12.571 --> 26:13.833
You understand me?
You could've drowned.

26:13.876 --> 26:16.096
-Ben? Ben?
-What were you thinking?

26:16.139 --> 26:17.271
-Huh?
-Ben?

26:17.314 --> 26:18.402
Uncle Ben, I...

26:18.446 --> 26:20.143
-What?
-Honey, it's okay.

26:20.187 --> 26:21.492
What?

26:22.581 --> 26:24.626
Okay.

26:24.670 --> 26:26.062
After I almost drowned

26:26.106 --> 26:28.151
my uncle did a total 180.

26:28.195 --> 26:29.849
It like, broke his brain

26:29.892 --> 26:31.677
that I had never been
taught how to swim.

26:31.720 --> 26:34.636
Or been to Disneyland
or had a piece of broccoli.

26:34.680 --> 26:37.160
He always convinced that
he and my aunt could save me

26:37.204 --> 26:38.640
from my sad childhood

26:38.684 --> 26:40.642
like they had saved me
from that pool.

26:40.686 --> 26:42.296
I got ya.

26:42.339 --> 26:44.907
Okay.

26:44.951 --> 26:46.169
I'm gonna call her.

26:50.347 --> 26:52.523
Bea coming to live with us
is the right thing.

26:52.567 --> 26:55.744
-Absolutely. Absolutely.
-Yeah.

26:55.788 --> 26:58.051
It's all about
how you present it.

26:58.094 --> 26:59.835
I'm sure your sister's gonna
understand.

26:59.879 --> 27:01.054
Yeah.

27:08.539 --> 27:10.411
Turns out, my mom didn't.

27:10.454 --> 27:14.197
She called 9-1-1 and told them
someone was trying to steal me.

27:14.241 --> 27:15.764
I over heard my aunt
tell the cops

27:15.808 --> 27:19.289
she just wanted me
to have a normal life.

27:19.333 --> 27:21.857
For my aunt and uncle,
that meant private school.

27:21.901 --> 27:23.859
Plank's constant is equal to

27:23.903 --> 27:27.428
6.63 times 10 to
the negative 34 joule seconds.

27:27.471 --> 27:29.735
At first, my dad refused
the tuition money.

27:29.778 --> 27:32.346
but Grandma Loretta
made him accept.

27:32.389 --> 27:34.087
She figured if I got
knocked up in high school

27:34.130 --> 27:37.873
like she did, at least
it would be by a rich kid.

27:37.917 --> 27:40.049
Bea, I'm still waiting
on those college applications.

27:40.093 --> 27:42.748
I know, I know,
never leave that till tomorrow

27:42.791 --> 27:46.055
what you can do today.
I'm on it, Mr. V.

27:46.099 --> 27:48.754
While my family was busy
worrying about my future

27:48.797 --> 27:51.104
I was just trying to
balance work, school

27:51.147 --> 27:52.801
and caring for my parents.

27:52.845 --> 27:54.977
There I was.

27:55.021 --> 27:58.154
You know, I was like
in the middle of the road.

27:58.198 --> 28:02.071
You know, like, half dead.

28:02.115 --> 28:06.510
And, uh, I was,
I was looking up at the sun.

28:07.947 --> 28:11.515
But, uh,
it-it-it wasn't the sun.

28:11.559 --> 28:15.258
No. It was the light.

28:15.302 --> 28:17.783
-It's true. He saw the light.
-Yeah.

28:17.826 --> 28:19.175
Yeah.

28:19.219 --> 28:21.264
Then when I woke up

28:21.308 --> 28:24.833
part of the car was, uh,
was on top of me

28:24.877 --> 28:27.140
and I just, felt it.

28:27.183 --> 28:28.707
I just, you know, I'm muscle.

28:28.750 --> 28:31.318
That thing
and I-I just threw it off.

28:31.361 --> 28:34.016
'Cause, you know,
even since I was a kid

28:34.060 --> 28:38.629
I was built like a,
you know, brick crap house.

28:41.241 --> 28:43.983
I don't know what this
has to do with my question.

28:47.856 --> 28:50.032
Well, you asked me...

28:50.076 --> 28:54.341
why I am not scared
or-or sad about Bea.

28:56.473 --> 28:57.910
That's because...

28:58.911 --> 29:00.695
you know, that day...

29:02.218 --> 29:04.655
Jesus told me
he had my back.

29:06.745 --> 29:09.138
And-and my Bea,
she's a part of me,

29:09.182 --> 29:11.401
so...

29:11.445 --> 29:13.099
you know,
he's got her back, too.

29:13.142 --> 29:14.230
Amen.

29:14.274 --> 29:15.318
That's me.

29:15.362 --> 29:17.451
A real child of God.

29:17.494 --> 29:19.670
Good evening and God bless.

29:19.714 --> 29:22.282
I'm selling tickets
for my school's fund raiser.

29:22.325 --> 29:24.806
The winner gets two tickets
to see Celine Dion

29:24.850 --> 29:26.808
and whoever sells the most
raffle tickets

29:26.852 --> 29:29.768
gets to go on our senior trip
to Disneyland for free.

29:29.811 --> 29:32.118
So, it's a win-win really.

29:38.646 --> 29:41.431
Hi, I'm selling raffle tickets
are you interested?

29:41.475 --> 29:43.738
-I'm interested in some band.
-They're for Celine Dion.

29:43.782 --> 29:45.696
And they are five dollars
for one raffle ticket.

29:45.740 --> 29:47.220
-Maybe we can go together?
-No.

29:47.263 --> 29:49.439
-No? Hey! I was gonna sell--
-What?

29:49.483 --> 29:50.789
There are like
a million pedophiles.

29:50.832 --> 29:53.182
Thanks. Sorry.

29:58.274 --> 29:59.798
I'm so sorry.

30:01.451 --> 30:03.366
This is all my fault.

30:10.330 --> 30:11.940
Are you Bea's doctor?

30:11.984 --> 30:16.205
No. I'm from child
and family services.

30:16.249 --> 30:19.513
I'm trying to figure out
what happened to Bea.

30:19.556 --> 30:21.341
Do you mind
if we talk for a second?

30:26.302 --> 30:28.609
So, Bea didn't tell you
where she was going?

30:28.652 --> 30:29.784
Nope.

30:31.873 --> 30:33.744
Feeling nervous.

30:33.788 --> 30:35.442
Nope.

30:35.485 --> 30:36.660
Guilty?

30:36.704 --> 30:39.489
No. Why would I feel guilty?

30:39.533 --> 30:41.143
Oh, I heard you tell Bea

30:41.187 --> 30:42.797
that you thought
it was all your fault.

30:42.841 --> 30:44.625
No, I didn't.

30:44.668 --> 30:47.193
Okay. I must've misheard.

30:48.585 --> 30:50.849
One more question.

30:50.892 --> 30:52.328
Does Bea drink?

30:52.372 --> 30:55.201
A little bit
too much sometimes?

30:55.244 --> 30:56.898
I'm not here
to get her in trouble but...

30:58.682 --> 31:00.380
she had quite a bit of
alcohol in her system

31:00.423 --> 31:01.468
when she was admitted and--

31:01.511 --> 31:03.078
No, no, no,
that's impossible.

31:03.122 --> 31:04.297
Bea doesn't drink.

31:04.340 --> 31:05.864
Her dad was hit
by a drunk driver

31:05.907 --> 31:07.691
so she was like,
totally against it.

31:12.435 --> 31:14.568
So, what do you all
do for fun?

31:14.611 --> 31:16.396
I don't know. Hang out.

31:18.398 --> 31:20.443
Any place in particular?

31:23.969 --> 31:25.927
I told you to wear
something warmer.

31:25.971 --> 31:28.974
Well, this outfit get helps me
get all the rich pedos.

31:29.017 --> 31:30.801
Can we please just go home?

31:30.845 --> 31:33.282
What? No. I have...
I barely sold any tickets.

31:33.326 --> 31:36.024
So, what?
Why do you care so much?

31:36.068 --> 31:38.635
Well, I heard Esther Lawrence
tell everyone at lunch

31:38.679 --> 31:40.420
that no one could sell more
tickets than her

31:40.463 --> 31:42.422
and I want everyone to know
what a lying bitch she is.

31:42.465 --> 31:44.946
-And then I want her to die.
-Bea!

31:44.990 --> 31:46.556
Okay, I don't want her to die.

31:46.600 --> 31:48.254
I just want her to get
chlamydia.

31:49.516 --> 31:51.344
What?
It's totally curable.

31:51.387 --> 31:53.215
She's probably already
had it before.

31:53.259 --> 31:55.000
Are you ever gonna
get over it?

31:55.043 --> 31:56.566
Nia, she called you
Kim Jong-un

31:56.610 --> 31:57.785
in front of
the whole football team.

31:57.828 --> 31:58.873
Yeah, thank you. I remember.

31:58.917 --> 32:00.005
I was there.

32:03.878 --> 32:06.228
Ugh, I'm gonna be late...

32:06.272 --> 32:07.403
for work.

32:08.796 --> 32:11.016
Ah, pool duty calls.

32:11.059 --> 32:12.321
Shall we?

32:28.250 --> 32:31.993
♪ You think it's funny
how the little things ♪

32:32.037 --> 32:33.647
♪ Make you sad

32:33.690 --> 32:36.955
♪ But even though
I've seen it all ♪

32:36.998 --> 32:41.176
♪ Whispers pick
through your skin ♪

32:41.220 --> 32:44.310
♪ Places don't remember like

32:44.353 --> 32:47.878
♪ The markings on your neck

32:47.922 --> 32:51.186
♪ Once you're gone
it's like you never ♪

32:51.230 --> 32:53.797
♪ Really took a breath

32:55.799 --> 32:58.759
♪ If the universe obliges

32:58.802 --> 33:02.154
♪ Stars will fall
upon mankind ♪

33:02.197 --> 33:04.678
♪ It's only part of time

33:04.721 --> 33:09.726
♪ But even that is far behind

33:12.338 --> 33:13.992
♪ You think it's funny

33:14.035 --> 33:17.604
♪ How the clothes
you wear are there ♪

33:17.647 --> 33:21.521
♪ But the faces
in turn are not ♪

33:21.564 --> 33:25.003
♪ As easily compared

33:25.046 --> 33:28.136
♪ Eyes cannot pierce
through the way ♪

33:28.180 --> 33:31.835
♪ That only you can do

33:31.879 --> 33:34.055
♪ But really far away

33:34.099 --> 33:38.364
♪ It's like they wanted
you to say ♪

33:42.237 --> 33:45.719
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh

33:49.114 --> 33:52.943
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪

34:05.956 --> 34:08.002
Dad, don't forget you have
a dermatologist appointment

34:08.046 --> 34:09.656
today at noon.

34:09.699 --> 34:11.179
Also, rent's due,
so can you deposit

34:11.223 --> 34:13.399
mom's disability check?

34:13.442 --> 34:15.053
And make sure
they tip you out today.

34:15.096 --> 34:16.489
They're supposed to give
the bussers five percent.

34:16.532 --> 34:18.404
Don't spend it on slots.

34:18.447 --> 34:20.493
♪ I don't care who sees ♪

34:20.536 --> 34:23.844
