52:27.970 --> 52:28.928
Yeah!

52:31.191 --> 52:34.586
-Sorry about all that.
-Don't be.

52:36.457 --> 52:40.983
I-I think it's kinda cool
that your dad is so into Jesus.

52:41.027 --> 52:42.333
-You better?
-Yeah.

52:42.376 --> 52:43.943
Your dad is my inspiration.

52:46.685 --> 52:49.296
When I was sick...

52:49.340 --> 52:50.602
it might have been nice to have

52:50.645 --> 52:53.431
something like that
to believe in.

52:53.474 --> 52:55.476
Maybe it would have
been less scary.

52:56.738 --> 52:59.219
♪ You're my baby

52:59.263 --> 53:01.308
♪ You're my baby...

53:04.093 --> 53:06.879
I never hear my parents
laugh like that.

53:06.922 --> 53:08.185
At least not
when they're together.

53:08.228 --> 53:10.187
Oh, they always laugh.

53:10.230 --> 53:12.928
Even at the most
inappropriate times.

53:12.972 --> 53:14.887
Like my Uncle Fred's funeral.

53:19.631 --> 53:21.720
♪ Let's move the Bakers
family to... ♪♪

53:21.763 --> 53:24.375
Have you thought
at all about prom?

53:24.418 --> 53:25.811
Yeah, I don't know.
It's a little...

53:25.854 --> 53:28.988
It's a little stereotypical
teen for me.

53:29.031 --> 53:31.904
Generally-generally speaking.

53:31.947 --> 53:35.821
Well, this basic bitch
can't wait to go.

53:35.864 --> 53:41.870
-But, only if it's with you.
-Okay.

53:41.914 --> 53:45.787
There I was. With a boyfriend.
Going to prom.

53:45.831 --> 53:47.311
Hey, Ethan, come on.
Get over here, man.

53:47.354 --> 53:50.270
I wanna-I wanna play one of
my originals.

53:50.314 --> 53:52.359
-Oh, boy. Mm-hmm.
-An original?

53:52.403 --> 53:54.883
And for the first time
since I was ten,

53:54.927 --> 53:56.755
I'm not embarrassed
about my life.

54:00.367 --> 54:04.110
♪ Taking all my money
never comin' back ♪

54:04.153 --> 54:09.246
♪ Oh ooh ooh here I go

54:09.289 --> 54:13.598
♪ Racin' in the wind
in my very own ♪

54:13.641 --> 54:17.123
♪ Ridin' super fast
but I'm actually not... ♪

54:20.431 --> 54:21.606
♪ In a car

54:26.393 --> 54:28.917
Attention. The Henderson
Community Pool

54:28.961 --> 54:31.311
is closing in five minutes.

54:31.355 --> 54:32.312
You work here?

54:35.272 --> 54:37.491
No, Esther,
I'm picking up your trash

54:37.535 --> 54:39.319
because I don't work here.

54:39.363 --> 54:40.625
I really think you should

54:40.668 --> 54:43.192
reconsider the free trip
to Disney.

54:43.236 --> 54:45.543
I wasn't really embarrassed
about anything anymore.

54:45.586 --> 54:46.544
You're right.

54:47.936 --> 54:49.982
Because I'm poor.

54:50.025 --> 54:54.769
So poor that sometimes I help
pay rent for the tiny house

54:54.813 --> 54:57.990
I live in
with my disabled parents.

54:58.033 --> 54:59.818
But you knew that
because you told everyone

54:59.861 --> 55:01.950
in fifth grade
that they were retarded.

55:03.691 --> 55:05.476
You may have more money
than me,

55:05.519 --> 55:06.868
but I have an IQ of one-forty,

55:06.912 --> 55:09.567
and the boyfriend
you wish you had.

55:09.610 --> 55:12.613
And I know that because Gina
said that you told everyone

55:12.657 --> 55:13.788
you'd let him finger you
in front of

55:13.832 --> 55:16.356
the whole football team
if he asked.

55:16.400 --> 55:18.184
She also let it slip
that you and Andy

55:18.227 --> 55:19.577
haven't had sex since
the party.

55:20.708 --> 55:22.057
So...

55:22.101 --> 55:23.276
-Hi.
-How you doin'?

55:27.628 --> 55:32.677
-Mmm. shall we?
-Sure.

55:32.720 --> 55:34.722
-Bye, ladies.
-Bye, Esther.

55:38.335 --> 55:40.075
-That's obviously not true.
-Really?

55:41.990 --> 55:43.644
Life was good.

55:43.688 --> 55:45.298
I made enough money
to go to Disney

55:45.342 --> 55:46.691
and buy a dress for prom.

55:48.388 --> 55:50.303
I was kicking ass at school.

55:51.522 --> 55:53.088
Track had never been better.

55:55.656 --> 55:57.789
And Ethan and I
were getting close.

55:57.832 --> 55:59.225
Wait, wait.

56:01.053 --> 56:03.142
I'm not losing my virginity
in the back of a car

56:03.185 --> 56:05.753
like every other woman
in my family.

56:05.797 --> 56:08.147
-Got it?
-Got it.

56:08.190 --> 56:09.540
Really close.

56:09.583 --> 56:10.541
Screw it.

56:20.377 --> 56:21.943
Good morning, Bea.

56:21.987 --> 56:24.076
I wanted to chat with you
about something.

56:24.119 --> 56:27.122
I swear that was not me
in the parking lot last night.

56:27.166 --> 56:30.169
I've-I've never even
been in a Land Rover before.

56:30.212 --> 56:33.259
What are you talking about?
You know what?

56:33.302 --> 56:35.261
-I don't wanna know.
-Good.

56:35.304 --> 56:38.264
I wanted to talk about your
feelings toward college.

56:38.307 --> 56:41.006
Who said I had any
feelings about it?

56:41.049 --> 56:45.053
Actions speak louder than words,
Bea. What are you doing?

56:45.097 --> 56:47.839
Looking for the motivational
poster you're reading from.

56:47.882 --> 56:50.276
Bea, I'm serious.
You have really good grades,

56:50.319 --> 56:53.322
good SAT scores, and I have to
hound you just to get you

56:53.366 --> 56:55.629
to finish your application.

56:55.673 --> 56:57.718
And now I see,
you've only applied

56:57.762 --> 57:01.200
to local community colleges.

57:01.243 --> 57:02.375
Why limit yourself?

57:05.944 --> 57:09.469
Look, I know things at home
look a bit different

57:09.513 --> 57:10.775
for you than most kids here.

57:10.818 --> 57:12.472
Well, then you should know then

57:12.516 --> 57:14.822
why my parents can't
afford most schools.

57:14.866 --> 57:18.391
I-I don't mean to overstep, but
perhaps whoever's helping you

57:18.435 --> 57:21.916
with tuition now, maybe
could help you with college?

57:21.960 --> 57:23.483
Ugh. The last thing I need is

57:23.527 --> 57:25.311
more charity from my
aunt and uncle.

57:25.354 --> 57:27.269
I mean, they already keep
a photo of me on their mantle

57:27.313 --> 57:30.490
next to the starving kid
in Africa they sponsor.

57:30.534 --> 57:31.491
Really?

57:33.014 --> 57:36.365
Um, maybe financial aid
is another option.

57:36.409 --> 57:38.890
Y-you know, with your grades
and extra-curriculars,

57:38.933 --> 57:40.979
you have a shot at getting
a really good package.

57:41.022 --> 57:43.503
Yeah, it's not just
about the money.

57:43.547 --> 57:47.376
Look, I gotta, I gotta go.
I'm gonna be late.

57:47.420 --> 57:50.336
Ah, wait-wait-wait. Okay, okay.
Wait, just sit, alright?

57:52.251 --> 57:54.471
Alright, why don't we
just take a step back

57:54.514 --> 57:56.647
from reality for a second?

57:56.690 --> 57:58.126
If you could go to a school,

57:58.170 --> 57:59.911
anywhere in the world,
where would you go?

58:02.522 --> 58:04.350
Honestly, I don't know.

58:04.393 --> 58:06.831
I've never really seriously
thought about it.

58:06.874 --> 58:09.268
Okay. Um, what's your
favorite subject?

58:09.311 --> 58:13.054
Mm, I... Science.
I like astronomy a lot.

58:13.098 --> 58:16.710
That's a great start. I have...

58:16.754 --> 58:19.278
Where is it?

58:19.321 --> 58:22.803
Here are some great schools
with excellent science programs.

58:24.588 --> 58:25.937
Tips and tricks.

58:25.980 --> 58:27.329
I'd be more than happy to write

58:27.373 --> 58:28.592
a letter of recommendation
for you.

58:30.289 --> 58:34.032
Hmm. These are all really
good schools.

58:34.075 --> 58:36.121
You think
I could actually get in?

58:36.164 --> 58:38.123
Shoot for the stars,
you'll hit the roof.

58:39.516 --> 58:41.474
That's kind of a messed
up saying.

58:41.518 --> 58:43.781
Bea, a little more
energy and effort

58:43.824 --> 58:45.565
and I think you could
get into any place.

58:47.132 --> 58:49.482
You're an exceptional student.

58:49.526 --> 58:52.790
Thanks, Mr. V.
I'll think about it.

58:52.833 --> 58:56.097
Alright. Hey, exciting stuff.

58:56.141 --> 58:58.099
Yeah, well, well. Whatever.

58:59.710 --> 59:00.667
I guess.

59:13.027 --> 59:15.160
Do you ever wonder
what you're gonna do

59:15.203 --> 59:17.031
with the rest of your life?

59:18.859 --> 59:21.949
No, I've always had too much
to worry about right now

59:21.993 --> 59:24.778
to worry about the future.

59:24.822 --> 59:25.779
Why?

59:27.085 --> 59:29.696
I was just thinking...

59:29.740 --> 59:35.572
I don't really have like
a...goal in life.

59:35.615 --> 59:39.053
I mean, i-it was beating cancer,
but I already did that.

59:40.838 --> 59:42.753
And I thought you wanted to
take over for your dad?

59:44.189 --> 59:46.147
You think my dream
was porta potties?

59:48.497 --> 59:51.936
Well, I... You know, I think
you can do anything you want.

59:53.372 --> 59:55.896
Why? 'Cause my parents are rich

59:55.940 --> 59:58.203
and they'll support me
no matter what?

59:58.246 --> 1:00:01.641
No. Because you're amazing.

1:00:10.519 --> 1:00:14.045
♪ I remember when we
first met and everything... ♪

1:00:14.088 --> 1:00:16.482
-Where are you going?
-What do you think?

1:00:18.049 --> 1:00:19.006
Uh...

1:00:20.704 --> 1:00:23.097
Yep. I'm getting in.

1:00:23.141 --> 1:00:25.622
♪ Leave a message on your...

1:00:25.665 --> 1:00:27.885
We're gonna really
regret this soon.

1:00:27.928 --> 1:00:28.886
Alright.

1:00:31.018 --> 1:00:32.672
I'm doing it.

1:00:34.674 --> 1:00:38.373
Oh, my gosh! Oh!

1:00:38.417 --> 1:00:40.724
-Oh, shit! It's so cold.
-Oh!

1:00:40.767 --> 1:00:43.901
♪ Wish I could follow you

1:00:46.120 --> 1:00:48.688
♪ Into the shores

1:00:50.734 --> 1:00:52.300
I think you're amazing, too.

1:00:57.741 --> 1:01:00.047
♪ Freedom

1:01:00.091 --> 1:01:03.964
♪ Run away to live

1:01:04.008 --> 1:01:07.011
♪ Freedom

1:01:07.054 --> 1:01:09.230
♪ Run away

1:01:09.274 --> 1:01:15.193
♪ Run away to live...

1:01:17.761 --> 1:01:19.327
Hi. Yep. Coming.

1:01:19.371 --> 1:01:20.502
Okay, great.

1:01:24.724 --> 1:01:26.204
Place is a mess.

1:01:26.247 --> 1:01:29.468
Dad, why didn't you
go grocery shopping?

1:01:29.511 --> 1:01:31.296
Because I'm taking a nap.

1:01:31.339 --> 1:01:33.864
-Can you take me to the store?
-I gotta go. Ask dad.

1:01:45.571 --> 1:01:49.967
-What about this one?
-Oh... That's hideous.

1:01:50.010 --> 1:01:52.709
-And two hundred bucks!
-Well, how much do you have?

1:01:55.102 --> 1:01:56.408
Have you heard of a debit card?

1:01:56.451 --> 1:01:57.844
Carrying cash like
that is dangerous.

1:01:57.888 --> 1:01:59.280
Well, I'm not eighteen yet.

1:01:59.324 --> 1:02:01.543
My parents would have to
co-sign for an account.

1:02:01.587 --> 1:02:04.198
-So?
-Well, so...

1:02:04.242 --> 1:02:06.026
One summer,
I made three hundred bucks

1:02:06.070 --> 1:02:08.463
selling lemonade and asked my
mom to put it into an account

1:02:08.507 --> 1:02:10.944
for me,
she spent it on slots instead.

1:02:12.990 --> 1:02:14.034
Hmmm.

1:02:15.166 --> 1:02:16.950
Hmm.

1:02:16.994 --> 1:02:19.779
-What about this one?
-Too slutty.

1:02:19.823 --> 1:02:20.867
Okay.

1:02:22.869 --> 1:02:24.828
-This one?
-Sluttier.

1:02:24.871 --> 1:02:27.265
Well, what is wrong
with sluttier?

1:02:27.308 --> 1:02:30.572
Let's slut it up.
I like it.

1:02:34.838 --> 1:02:37.275
Guys, here she comes.

1:02:37.318 --> 1:02:40.321
Hi. Uh, is there any way
you could buy us a six pack?

1:02:41.453 --> 1:02:42.410
You can keep the change.

1:02:57.817 --> 1:03:00.864
I'm sorry. Are you bored?

1:03:00.907 --> 1:03:03.301
I didn't say anything.

1:03:03.344 --> 1:03:04.302
Why are you mad?

1:03:06.870 --> 1:03:08.872
I'm not mad, but it's like,
I haven't seen you in like

1:03:08.915 --> 1:03:10.264
a month and you said that you
didn't want to go to

1:03:10.308 --> 1:03:11.744
prom, and now you are,
and I didn't get a date

1:03:11.788 --> 1:03:12.789
'cause you said that
we weren't gonna go

1:03:12.832 --> 1:03:14.268
and now I'm just like...stuck.

1:03:16.488 --> 1:03:19.534
Uh, I'm sorry.

1:03:19.578 --> 1:03:22.450
I wasn't planning on it,
it just...

1:03:22.494 --> 1:03:25.192
It just happened. What...

1:03:25.236 --> 1:03:26.280
what do you want me to do?

1:03:27.716 --> 1:03:30.676
-Don't go.
-Are you serious?

1:03:30.719 --> 1:03:32.591
Haven't you heard
of hos before bros?

1:03:32.634 --> 1:03:34.811
No. Because that's not a thing.

1:03:34.854 --> 1:03:38.075
-You're being ridiculous.
-Fine, then. I'll leave.

1:03:38.118 --> 1:03:40.817
-Wait, you can't leave.
-Don't tell me what to do.

1:03:40.860 --> 1:03:42.122
You're always telling
me what to do!

1:03:42.166 --> 1:03:43.950
What is that supposed to mean?

1:03:43.994 --> 1:03:45.473
Why don't you figure it out
while you walk home?

1:03:45.517 --> 1:03:47.475
-Fine, I will!
-Fine.

1:03:47.519 --> 1:03:50.304
And you know what?
For the record,

1:03:50.348 --> 1:03:52.959
I don't think I'm the reason
you don't have a date to prom.

1:03:55.875 --> 1:03:57.529
Wait!

1:03:57.572 --> 1:03:59.444
I didn't mean it.

1:03:59.487 --> 1:04:00.445
Come back!

1:04:03.187 --> 1:04:05.232
Okay... What are you looking at?

1:04:09.062 --> 1:04:10.020
Oh.

1:04:13.980 --> 1:04:16.809
I didn't think I could feel
any worse in that moment.

1:04:18.942 --> 1:04:20.726
But everything happens
for a reason.

1:04:22.293 --> 1:04:23.642
Godzilla?

1:04:23.685 --> 1:04:26.166
Godzilla! My baby!

1:04:26.210 --> 1:04:28.125
Hi. Hi.

1:04:30.562 --> 1:04:32.869
What're you,
what're doing here?

1:04:33.782 --> 1:04:34.740
Hey!

1:04:36.046 --> 1:04:38.265
Honey, I missed you.

1:04:38.309 --> 1:04:40.006
But at least
I could make this right.

1:04:40.050 --> 1:04:41.225
You're coming with me.

1:04:43.923 --> 1:04:47.492
My baby! Ah!
You're coming with me.

1:04:50.756 --> 1:04:52.105
You did the right thing.
I think we're...

1:04:52.149 --> 1:04:54.325
I think we're good now.
Go back to work.

1:04:57.850 --> 1:04:59.765
Where is my wife?
Where is my Sharon?

1:04:59.808 --> 1:05:01.898
I need you to calm down, sir.
Look, she was selling

1:05:01.941 --> 1:05:03.595
alcohol to minors,
and it wasn't the first time.

1:05:03.638 --> 1:05:04.944
-No, you can't arrest her!
-She was selling alcohol.

1:05:04.988 --> 1:05:06.467
She admitted to it.
We're gonna take her in.

1:05:06.511 --> 1:05:07.904
Look, you don't understand.
Look, you-you...

1:05:07.947 --> 1:05:09.253
Unless you wanna get
back there with her.

1:05:09.296 --> 1:05:11.081
Hey, put you're hand
behind your back!

1:05:11.124 --> 1:05:12.952
Look, she's not gonna
be good back there.

1:05:12.996 --> 1:05:14.693
-You gotta... Okay. Okay!
-Calm down. Hey.

1:05:14.736 --> 1:05:16.347
Look, she can't be there
alone, alright.

1:05:16.390 --> 1:05:17.739
-She won't be. You're goin'...
-I gotta go with her.

1:05:17.783 --> 1:05:19.132
Calm down.

1:05:19.176 --> 1:05:22.527
Okay, we're home.

1:05:26.661 --> 1:05:28.576
I'm sorry they didn't
take care of you.

1:05:30.578 --> 1:05:33.277
Ugh. You smell like hot trash.

1:05:34.713 --> 1:05:36.280
Hey, you guys.

1:05:36.323 --> 1:05:38.195
Look who I found.

1:05:39.674 --> 1:05:40.632
Hello?

1:05:42.416 --> 1:05:44.027
Oh. Okay.

1:05:49.815 --> 1:05:50.772
What?!

1:05:52.470 --> 1:05:53.427
What?!

1:05:55.255 --> 1:05:56.648
How much is bail?

1:06:16.537 --> 1:06:19.323
You know, I mean,
jail ain't that bad.

1:06:19.366 --> 1:06:23.849
The food was decent, right?
An-and-and you don't gotta work.

1:06:25.720 --> 1:06:27.896
Mom, can you turn the TV off?

1:06:27.940 --> 1:06:31.161
I don't normally do this.
I really like you...

1:06:31.204 --> 1:06:33.728
We all need to have
a serious talk.

1:06:33.772 --> 1:06:38.124
You found him!
Oh, my good boy!

1:06:38.168 --> 1:06:40.344
He's back!
What a good boy!

1:06:42.868 --> 1:06:44.739
You are the best little boy.

1:06:44.783 --> 1:06:47.133
-Don't you dare run away again.
-Yeah.

1:06:47.177 --> 1:06:48.526
He didn't, mom.

1:06:51.094 --> 1:06:52.008
I gave him away.

1:06:53.705 --> 1:06:54.880
Well, why would you do that?

1:06:56.534 --> 1:06:57.491
I, uh...

1:06:59.580 --> 1:07:01.800
I wanted him to have
a real family.

1:07:05.543 --> 1:07:08.154
I mean, we are a real family.

1:07:11.288 --> 1:07:13.072
Right.

1:07:13.116 --> 1:07:14.552
Right.

1:07:14.595 --> 1:07:17.903
-And you're real parents?
-Yeah, we are.

1:07:19.948 --> 1:07:22.951
Well, real dads don't miss
their kid's track meets

1:07:22.995 --> 1:07:25.693
to race toy cars.

1:07:25.737 --> 1:07:28.957
And real moms don't steal
their kid's money

1:07:29.001 --> 1:07:30.307
and blow it on slots.

1:07:30.350 --> 1:07:32.744
And real parents
don't need their kids

1:07:32.787 --> 1:07:35.399
to bail them out of jail!

1:07:35.442 --> 1:07:38.271
You owe me five $500.

1:07:38.315 --> 1:07:40.056
That money was for me!

1:07:41.796 --> 1:07:44.103
I-I don't have five hundred
bucks, Bea.

1:07:44.147 --> 1:07:45.800
Well, then,
when do you get paid?

1:07:50.066 --> 1:07:51.023
Dad?

1:07:53.330 --> 1:07:56.550
The race track's been
kinda slow lately, you know.

1:07:57.856 --> 1:07:58.813
Wai-wait.

1:07:59.901 --> 1:08:02.034
Did... did they let you go?

1:08:04.689 --> 1:08:05.646
When?

1:08:08.693 --> 1:08:09.911
I don't know.
Like, a few months ago.

1:08:09.955 --> 1:08:11.435
Why didn't you tell me?

1:08:11.478 --> 1:08:13.132
Because I got a new job already.

1:08:13.176 --> 1:08:16.092
-Wh-where?
-At Lyft.

1:08:16.135 --> 1:08:18.572
I mean,
as soon as I fix my truck.

1:08:18.616 --> 1:08:20.618
Okay, okay...

1:08:20.661 --> 1:08:23.838
Between mom's paycheck,
and disability

1:08:23.882 --> 1:08:26.972
we should, we should fine
until you get a real job.

1:08:28.321 --> 1:08:30.149
Your mama ain't getting
disability.

1:08:30.193 --> 1:08:32.282
What? Why?

1:08:32.325 --> 1:08:33.674
Because I cancelled it.

1:08:33.718 --> 1:08:36.242
Oh! Do you know
how long it took me

1:08:36.286 --> 1:08:37.939
to get mom signed up for that?

1:08:37.983 --> 1:08:39.419
Why would you do that?

1:08:39.463 --> 1:08:41.378
Because your mother
is not disabled.

1:08:41.421 --> 1:08:44.859
Oh, that's right. I'm sorry,
I forgot. She's special!

1:08:44.903 --> 1:08:48.776
Yes, she is.
We all are.

1:08:48.820 --> 1:08:52.171
My God!
Dad, that isn't a compliment!

1:08:52.215 --> 1:08:55.000
Do you not know
what that word means?

1:08:55.043 --> 1:08:57.959
Special is just the word
people use in this family

1:08:58.003 --> 1:09:02.050
because they can't admit that
you and mom are both retarded!

1:09:02.094 --> 1:09:04.357
-Ahh!
-Oh!

1:09:04.401 --> 1:09:06.403
Grandma Loretta was right.

1:09:06.446 --> 1:09:09.232
They never should've
let you have kids.

1:09:09.275 --> 1:09:11.843
We'd all be better off
if I wasn't alive.

1:09:23.246 --> 1:09:24.725
I'm not proud of what I said.

1:09:25.944 --> 1:09:26.901
But isn't it true?

1:09:27.989 --> 1:09:29.339
Do I even wanna wake up?

1:09:32.211 --> 1:09:35.780
What is that?
Is that "the" light?

1:09:35.823 --> 1:09:38.217
Am I dead? Because I was just
posing a question.

1:09:38.261 --> 1:09:41.220
I-I do. I-I want to wake up.

1:09:41.264 --> 1:09:44.876
Wait, where'd it go?
Am I going to hell?

1:09:47.095 --> 1:09:49.707
Jesus! That's bright.

1:09:49.750 --> 1:09:51.883
Well, her pupils are reacting.

1:09:51.926 --> 1:09:53.972
Ah! Thank you. I'm alive.

1:09:54.015 --> 1:09:55.365
I-is that a good thing?

1:09:56.844 --> 1:09:58.237
Would you all mind
taking a step back?

1:09:58.281 --> 1:10:00.761
-Yeah, give the man some space.
-Sorry.

1:10:02.676 --> 1:10:05.505
As I was saying, her pupils are
constricting, which is good.

1:10:05.549 --> 1:10:07.159
But I'd liked to see
quicker reactivity.

1:10:07.203 --> 1:10:08.508
Sorry, what does that mean?

1:10:08.552 --> 1:10:10.380
It's common in
traumatic brain injuries.

1:10:10.423 --> 1:10:12.817
She has a traumatic
brain injury?

1:10:12.860 --> 1:10:14.732
Oh, God! She's gonna end up
just like her father.

1:10:14.775 --> 1:10:16.864
-Hey!
-Ma... Ma, it's okay.

1:10:16.908 --> 1:10:18.518
Oh, God! I'm gonna
end up like my father.

1:10:18.562 --> 1:10:20.346
Will she?

1:10:20.390 --> 1:10:21.826
I don't know your medical
history, but if she does have

1:10:21.869 --> 1:10:23.567
a TBI, they range in severity.

1:10:23.610 --> 1:10:24.959
Some people make
a full recovery.

1:10:25.003 --> 1:10:26.831
And some don't?

1:10:26.874 --> 1:10:27.919
It depends on the severity.

1:10:29.964 --> 1:10:32.663
-I'll check back soon.
-Thank you, doctor.

1:10:32.706 --> 1:10:34.621
My whole life, I've been
torn between wanting

1:10:34.665 --> 1:10:38.625
to get away from my parents
and wanting to care for them.

1:10:38.669 --> 1:10:40.192
Now, I can't do either.

1:10:40.236 --> 1:10:41.585
In our follow-up meeting
you said

1:10:41.628 --> 1:10:43.543
you wanted to apply to UCLA.

1:10:43.587 --> 1:10:46.416
But you never finished
your application.

1:10:46.459 --> 1:10:48.287
-Why?
-Because I'm not going.

1:10:54.598 --> 1:10:55.990
What does the poster
behind you say?

1:10:57.905 --> 1:10:59.690
"Hang in there, dood!"

1:10:59.733 --> 1:11:01.866
No, dood.
The one that says,

1:11:01.909 --> 1:11:04.738
"Don't be afraid to fail.
Be afraid not to try."

1:11:06.087 --> 1:11:07.872
I'm not afraid.

1:11:07.915 --> 1:11:08.960
And I have tried.

1:11:10.178 --> 1:11:12.180
But I can't...

1:11:12.224 --> 1:11:15.967
-You can.
-No, I mean, I can't leave.

1:11:17.490 --> 1:11:20.406
Ah... Nevada?
I-I don't understand, why?

1:11:20.450 --> 1:11:25.585
No, my parents, they... they
will literally die without me.

1:11:25.629 --> 1:11:27.631
Look... I...

1:11:27.674 --> 1:11:29.328
I know your parents
are going through

1:11:29.372 --> 1:11:30.808
some challenges,
but from what I understand--

1:11:30.851 --> 1:11:34.072
Okay, you-you don't
understand anything.

1:11:46.127 --> 1:11:48.086
Hey. Hey, you okay?

1:11:48.129 --> 1:11:50.001
Yeah, I'm fine. Why?

1:11:50.044 --> 1:11:51.045
'Cause you're crying.

1:11:52.395 --> 1:11:53.613
Wanna ditch?

1:11:53.657 --> 1:11:55.528
-My parents aren't home.
-Okay.

1:12:02.100 --> 1:12:04.494
Holy shit.

1:12:04.537 --> 1:12:06.322
Oh, my God,
I can't breathe.

1:12:09.368 --> 1:12:11.283
-Gonna miss you, weirdo.
-Hmm.

1:12:14.417 --> 1:12:18.943
Hey... I'm still gonna come
visit you every weekend.

1:12:18.986 --> 1:12:20.684
Well, you won't have to.

1:12:23.251 --> 1:12:24.427
Wait, are you
breaking up with me?

1:12:24.470 --> 1:12:27.604
